    <message>
      <heading>Sat Dec 16 (Tzeentch)   :: &amp;WTalents and Discovery&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>3</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>
I would like to encourage you all to use the Discovery policy for learning
new things or rediscovering lost talents. There is pretty good precedent
for this in the books with Canler discovering how to bond and Damer making
great strides in the area of Healing. Some things, such as the Healing, 
will require and inborn affinity for such things. Others, like perhaps
firesword, would just require study. If you would like to become involved
in such things you need to apply. For discovering things, you need to
write up the proposal first and mail it to me. If I have no problems with
it, I pass it on to Valkeria for approval. If both of us give the go ahead,
then you begin the discovery RP. This takes a minimum of four weeks of RP
which needs to be logged. At the end of that time period, the CRE will
review the RP and determine if there was success or failure, whether you
need more time or if it is just hopeless or whatnot. If what you want is
something that does not require study, but is simply an inborn ability
such as affinity for healing or the ability to read residues, you simply
apply to me. Write a fairly thorough explanation of how you would RP the
ability and what you would plan to do with it and such as that. Some of
these are rather simply things which only require my approval. Others, such
as ter'angreal or angreal creation, would require CRE approval as well plus
discovery RP to learn how to use them. In any event a simply mail of one
sentence along the lines of &quot;Me want balefire.&quot; is not going to result in
approval.

If there are any questions, y'all know my mudmail address.

Tze
</text>
    </message>
    <message>
      <heading>Thu Dec 28 (Tzeentch)   :: &amp;WOn-Farm RP&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>4</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>
If you are on the farm doing non-lesson RP and would like to be rewarded,
message me through tells or on the guild channel. I am generally willing
to watch the RP and award quest points. If I am not around, or if I am
busy with something else, you may also log the RP and send me a -cleaned-
log at kaith@cubsmvp.com. This goes for any RP, really, but in order to
encourage (not force) on-farm RP, the points awarded will be slightly
higher for on-farm. If you cannot log, or would prefer not to, you may
send me a brief synopsis of the RP. This will not generally result in as
many points, but will still garner some rewards.. in addition to the 
fun of the RP, that is.

Tze
</text>
    </message>
    <message>
      <heading>Sun Jun 23 (Tzeentch)   :: &amp;RLessons and Tests&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>5</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>
In order to encourage training, I am starting an incentive program. If you
give one of the required lessons and send me the log, I'll give you a QP.
You will get an additional 1 to 4 QP for it depending on the quality of the
lesson. If it is an optional lesson, these awards will be -doubled-.
HOWEVER, if you receive the minimum award (i.e. give a very low quality
lesson) you may have to retest before you will be allowed to continue
giving lessons.

Very soon I am going to do away with the Fully Trained subrank and turn it
into an Instructor subrank. This will not be an elite position, it will be
a work position. The teach gskill will be moved to the Trained subrank and
Instructor subrank will be given gskillset. Furthermore, anyone who is of
the Trained subrank can apply to me to become a recruiter. This will also
be noted in your subrank. These people will be given guilding permission and
some responsibility in helping people with their applications. If you have
any questions or suggestions, you all know how to reach me.

Tze
</text>
    </message>
