      <heading>Fri Aug  2 (Tzeentch)   :: &amp;BGSKILLS&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>6</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>
&amp;fNEW GUILD POLICY&amp;n

Since we -do- have the most powerful gskills on the MUD, we will be making
a slight change in the laughable name of balance. If you are guilded in
secondary guilds, you must choose between having BT gskills or those of
the secondary guild. The only exception will be those skills that do not
count against gskill totals such as language skills (codetalk, trolloc,
old tongue, etc). If these seems unfair, grab a chunk of perspective.
Rolling Ring is the only weave that does not have a damage cap of it's own.
Only the fight code's cap of 20000 affects it. This is oh.. 2.5 times the
max that thunderburst can do. It is going to be hard to convince me that I
am being unfair by not letting you add something like wardercombat into
that mix. If you want to say &quot;but wouldn't you ICly know these other skills?&quot;
I'm going to respond loudly that GSKILLS ARE NOT IC!

Thank you,

Mgmt
</text>
