      <header>&amp;WNew Recruiter Policy&amp;n</header>
      <slot>15</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>242803</author>
      <date>1052268817</date>
      <authorname>Tiekith</authorname>
      <text>The previous policy concerning recruiters has been repealed.  It was silly 
and arbitrary.  Whoever wrote that policy deserves a sound beating.  Try to 
be gentle...I bruise easily.  The new policy is as follows:

There is no more Recruiter tag.  Instead, you will simply be given guilding 
permissions.  If you have guilding permissions, you can do seeker RP.  If 
you do not have guilding permissions, you need to obtain permission from 
the GL in order to do seeker RP.  If you want guilding permissions, see 
Jephrey or myself, and we'll give you a three minute interview.  There is 
no rank requirement, and there is no activity requirement.

Questions regarding this new policy should be directed wherever you want to 
direct them, but they probably won't do any good unless you post them here 
or use mudmail or something.
-Tiekith
</text>
    </message>
